09:13.462 --> 09:15.492
[Voice-over] 911,
what's your emergency?

09:15.517 --> 09:17.242
-[Theodore] -I'd like to report a shooting.

09:17.494 --> 09:20.160
-[Voice-over] Is it happening now?
- [Theodore] No, but it will.

09:20.698 --> 09:22.964
An hour from now.
Parker Pharmacy.

09:22.988 --> 09:24.533
Hertel and Saranac.

09:24.558 --> 09:26.019
-[Voice-over] What's your name, sir?

09:27.188 --> 09:28.588
Has anyone been hurt?

09:38.673 --> 09:39.952
-That's okay, sir.

09:40.502 --> 09:41.782
I'll take care of that.

09:51.538 --> 09:52.545
[elevator dings]

09:52.569 --> 09:54.771
What is your firm's most valuable asset?

09:55.116 --> 09:58.396
Equities? Fixed incomes? Commodities?

09:59.522 --> 10:00.982
Human capital.

10:02.034 --> 10:04.101
Employ the absolute brightest,

10:04.995 --> 10:06.048
the most responsible.

10:06.578 --> 10:07.839
Make them stay.

10:08.643 --> 10:11.044
-They say if you want loyalty, get a dog.

10:13.773 --> 10:16.078
Supposedly no such thing in this business.

10:18.414 --> 10:20.147
Karl's quite the exception.

10:20.898 --> 10:22.157
Stellar performer.

10:22.182 --> 10:24.000
Been with us five years.

10:24.821 --> 10:26.059
Do you want to know why?

10:27.278 --> 10:28.703
We don't discriminate.

10:29.891 --> 10:31.602
-Soon you might have
to, Miss Freeman.

10:32.322 --> 10:36.118
Hiring practices have grown increasingly
sophisticated over the years.

10:36.430 --> 10:39.188
And with all due respect,
what your company does

10:39.213 --> 10:41.967
is quite...it's outdated.

10:43.272 --> 10:45.597
We've done an analysis
on a genetic profile

10:45.622 --> 10:47.048
of someone who works here.

10:49.936 --> 10:51.003
-Yes, of course.

10:55.283 --> 10:57.350
20% likelihood of Parkinson's,

10:58.455 --> 11:00.421
15% Alzheimerâ€™s

11:00.824 --> 11:03.510
30% OCD, 68% ADD-

11:03.535 --> 11:04.683
-I get it.

11:05.949 --> 11:07.194
Who are we talking about?

11:23.351 --> 11:24.351
How dare you?

11:26.429 --> 11:27.696
Is this even legal?

11:28.742 --> 11:30.475
- [Theodore] Well, it's...
- [Walter] We merely

11:30.476 --> 11:31.743
interpret the data.

11:31.767 --> 11:35.380
 We interpret it for you.
- What I meant was

11:36.162 --> 11:38.958
is it legal for you? Doctors.

11:41.567 --> 11:44.303
(door opens, closes)

11:46.873 --> 11:48.340
- What does she not get?

11:48.771 --> 11:51.044
We're already screening
embryos and cells.

11:54.200 --> 11:55.287
You okay?

11:55.312 --> 11:57.024
What's up with you in there?

11:58.567 --> 12:00.660
- We blew it, alright?
It's no big deal.

12:00.684 --> 12:02.684
- Yeah. It is when you
have child support.

12:02.708 --> 12:05.699
Right. All in the name of Lydia.

12:07.332 --> 12:08.366
-Screw you!

12:09.086 --> 12:11.490
What is it you think you
know about being a father?

12:12.102 --> 12:13.102
(phone rings)

12:14.359 --> 12:15.359
(clears throat)

12:16.178 --> 12:18.378
- Walter speaking.
-[Ms. Freeman] Dr. Hamilton,

12:19.108 --> 12:22.662
We're interviewing next week. Why
don't you and your partner drop by?

12:22.686 --> 12:23.868
-Stop the car.

12:23.892 --> 12:25.892
[Ms. Freeman] Are you
still there, Doctor?

12:26.274 --> 12:27.607
I said stop the car!

12:31.820 --> 12:34.002
(police scanner)

12:34.026 --> 12:36.386
(police scanner)

12:44.734 --> 12:46.952
Excuse me, sir, this is
a crime investigation.

12:46.976 --> 12:48.976
