15:09.626 --> 15:10.626
(footsteps)

15:15.628 --> 15:17.895
-I just knew I would
find you here.

15:20.208 --> 15:23.942
We used to come here to
pray when you saw things.

15:27.911 --> 15:30.178
-764 days.

15:31.435 --> 15:32.968
-Is it really that long?

15:34.974 --> 15:37.507
-Why did we stop coming
here, Aunt Kay?

15:40.096 --> 15:41.362
-You grew up, you...

15:42.197 --> 15:43.264
became a doctor,

15:45.361 --> 15:47.704
became obsessed with
finding the cure.

15:52.451 --> 15:54.878
- Half of all genetic
disorders are inherited.

15:57.795 --> 15:59.318
What were they like, my parents?

16:01.805 --> 16:06.839
Can't you acknowledge that there are
still some things in God's hands?

16:07.914 --> 16:08.914
- I know.

16:11.830 --> 16:14.524
The cause may be genetic, but the
solution doesn't have to be.

16:15.314 --> 16:17.567
I can just remove what's
causing the problem.

16:21.066 --> 16:23.230
(gentle music)

16:23.699 --> 16:26.245
(gentle music)

16:26.794 --> 16:28.596
- I want Corneal implants.

16:28.621 --> 16:31.849
- There's nothing wrong
with your eyes.

16:35.415 --> 16:36.415
- I get visions.

16:39.251 --> 16:41.251
Visions of the imminent future.

16:42.905 --> 16:44.314
- (laughs) Excuse me?

16:45.634 --> 16:47.234
If we were to lock eyes,

16:48.326 --> 16:50.686
and you were going to die
in the next 24 hours,

16:53.138 --> 16:54.938
I'd see your final moments.

16:56.630 --> 16:58.030
- Go someplace else.

16:58.055 --> 17:01.361
I'm not going to lose my license
over your magical story.

17:01.385 --> 17:03.385
(door opens, closes)

17:18.248 --> 17:19.800
- [Walter]-Hey. (laughs)

17:20.545 --> 17:21.545
You are here.

17:24.165 --> 17:25.165
How are you doing?

17:26.868 --> 17:28.502
Hungry? I'll take you to lunch.

17:29.963 --> 17:32.947
No, thanks. I've already eaten.

17:34.107 --> 17:35.507
You can watch me eat.

17:36.779 --> 17:37.779
Come on.

17:38.842 --> 17:40.772
(seagulls cawing)

17:41.240 --> 17:44.640
-[Theodore] Why are we here?
- Why weren't you at the funeral?

17:46.963 --> 17:48.358
I thought you were
going to buy me lunch.

17:57.990 --> 17:58.990
Here.

18:00.318 --> 18:01.694
Very generous of you.

18:01.719 --> 18:04.076
I was just starting
to get hungry.

18:05.545 --> 18:07.590
What happened the other
night at the pharmacy?

18:12.472 --> 18:13.472
- It's over.

18:16.050 --> 18:17.584
They found the shooter.

18:18.769 --> 18:20.369
- I searched your computer.

18:21.840 --> 18:24.523
I found a ton of research
on genetic para-normality.

18:27.183 --> 18:28.916
Whatever it is you're
trying to find,

18:29.108 --> 18:32.391
whatever it is you're
trying to hide,

18:33.284 --> 18:34.987
It's got something to do with Helen,

18:35.378 --> 18:37.838
the shooting. and Anna.

18:42.534 --> 18:43.963
- [Walter] Who else
knows about this?

18:44.634 --> 18:45.613
-[Theodore] My Aunt Kay.

18:47.097 --> 18:48.097
- Not even Anna?

18:50.429 --> 18:52.228
You don't trust her, do you?

18:52.253 --> 18:53.962
-It's not about trust.

18:53.986 --> 18:55.346
Then why'd you keep it from her?

18:55.371 --> 18:56.687
-Why'd I keep it from her?

18:57.241 --> 18:58.468
Why did I keep it from you?

18:58.493 --> 19:00.038
Why did I keep it from everyone?

19:03.815 --> 19:06.904
- Have you tried neuroleptics?
- For God's sake, Walter.

19:07.526 --> 19:09.393
These aren't hallucinations.

19:10.206 --> 19:11.810
- You have no idea
what it feels like

19:11.835 --> 19:13.705
to be running from
this your entire life.

19:14.692 --> 19:17.364
To know what's like, to
look inside someone's eyes

19:17.755 --> 19:20.206
and know they are going to die and there
is nothing you can do to stop it.

19:20.966 --> 19:22.863
You stopped Helen from dying.

19:22.888 --> 19:24.523
You altered her future.

19:25.015 --> 19:27.256
Theodore, you played God.

19:28.421 --> 19:31.086
You're capable of
either a lot of good,

19:32.573 --> 19:33.992
or a hell of a lot of bad.

19:39.789 --> 19:40.789
-[Theodore] The Panopticon.

19:41.969 --> 19:44.769
- 18th century prison.
- [Walter] Never heard of it.

19:46.069 --> 19:47.567
England's answer to controlling

19:47.592 --> 19:50.427
hundreds of inmates through
the eyes of a single watchman

19:50.452 --> 19:51.820
from a tower in the center.

19:52.288 --> 19:54.834
He sees everything, knows everything,

19:56.645 --> 19:57.645
but he's alone.

19:59.481 --> 20:00.757
Didn't take him too
long to figure out

20:00.782 --> 20:01.976
who the true prisoner is.

20:02.653 --> 20:04.070
- Why did you become a doctor?

20:05.000 --> 20:06.877
Because you enjoy
self-medication?

20:07.361 --> 20:08.827
Change of perspective.

20:11.376 --> 20:13.009
Better to bring life
into this world

20:13.034 --> 20:14.181
than to watch it go away.

20:14.823 --> 20:15.957
-Join the program.

20:16.800 --> 20:19.190
I'm sure you'll find other
freaks just like you.

20:20.777 --> 20:24.243
-Board-certified geneticist
claims to see the future.

20:26.231 --> 20:27.831
That sound right to you?

20:29.911 --> 20:32.244
- What's the worst that could happen?

20:33.777 --> 20:35.044
-They blacklist me.

20:36.160 --> 20:37.360
Revoke my license.

20:40.590 --> 20:43.323
Might as well give up on
finding the prescient gene.

20:50.493 --> 20:52.260
(gentle dramatic music)

20:52.284 --> 20:54.284
(gentle dramatic music)

21:21.572 --> 21:22.572
(gentle music)

21:24.931 --> 21:25.931
(gentle  music)

21:27.525 --> 21:29.925
- Here. enroll me in the program.

21:29.949 --> 21:32.885
(gentle  music)

21:40.701 --> 21:42.660
-[Theodore] I came here
to give you this.

21:42.685 --> 21:43.629
-You're quitting?

21:43.991 --> 21:45.225
- You can keep my share.

21:46.473 --> 21:47.978
You probably need
it more than me.

21:48.721 --> 21:49.826
- Read the papers?

21:50.590 --> 21:52.543
- I don't read too
well these days.

